
[1]laniard

   LANIARD, n. lan'yard.

   A short piece of rope or line, used for fastening something in ships,
   as the laniards of the gun-ports, of the buoy, of the cathook, &c., but
   especially used to extend the shrouds and stays of the masts, by their
   communication with the dead eyes, &c.
